Welcome to the NYC Urban Data Exploration Dashboard

This dashboard provides interactive visualizations of New York City's urban data from 2020 to 2025, spanning the COVID-19 pandemic and recovery period. Explore five interconnected visualizations that reveal patterns in transportation, public services, and urban life.

Data Collection Summary

  • 311 Service Requests: 956,602 records (2020-2025)
  • MTA Subway Ridership: 31,654 records (2020-2024)
  • TLC Taxi Trip Data: 1.9 million records (2020-2022)
  • Weather Data: Comprehensive coverage (2020-2025)
  • Events Data: Through March 2024

Urban Pulse

3D spatiotemporal density visualization showing the intensity of urban activities across NYC's geography.

Explore

Urban Network

Force-directed graph revealing relationships between urban systems, boroughs, and environmental factors.

Explore

Temporal Rhythm

Spiral visualization showing cyclical patterns in urban activities over hours, days, and months.

Explore

Urban Flow

Particle visualization depicting movement patterns and transportation corridors across the city.

Explore

Urban Symphony

Data sonification converting urban patterns into musical elements for an auditory experience of the city.

Explore

Key Insights

  • Clear visualization of COVID-19's impact with 80-90% reduction in transportation activity
  • Different recovery rates between taxi and subway systems
  • Distinctive spatial patterns showing Manhattan-centric transportation vs. distributed 311 calls
  • Strong correlations between weather factors and urban activities
  • Evolution of daily and weekly urban rhythms before, during, and after the pandemic
